article.headline: E. Michigan 61, Ball St. 51
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. (AP) -- Jared Axon scored 10 of his team-high 16 points in the second half to lead Eastern Michigan past Ball State 61-51 on Sunday. The Eagles (11-17, 5-9 Mid-American) finished the contest on a 20-7 run that included a seven-minute stretch in which they held the Cardinals scoreless. By the time Skip Mills ended the drought for Ball State with 1:20 left to play, the Eagles had built a 10-point lead. Craig Cashen sparked the run for Eastern Michigan with three 3-pointers and finished with 11 points on Senior Day. The Eagles' only other senior, Chris Knaub, scored a season-high nine points in his final game at the Convocation Center. Anthony Newell contributed a game-high 17 points for the Cardinals (9-19, 5-9), who also got 13 points from Mills. Ball State shot just 31 percent from the field in the first half but managed to make it to the break with the score tied at 24. Eastern shot better than 47 percent from the floor in the first half but was hampered by 14 turnovers. Newell's eight points to open the second half helped Ball State grab a seven-point lead before Eastern Michigan's defense clamped down for the remainder of the contest.
